  "title": "BIM Modeler / Electrical Drafter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Prepare and manage BIM models, shop drawings, and as-built drawings to support HDB projects, ensuring compliance with Singapore standards. Collaborate with cross-functional teams and participate in coordination meetings to drive project accuracy and efficiency.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and revise BIM models, shop drawings, and as-built drawings to meet project specifications and timelines</li><li>Collaborate with project managers, engineers, and on-site personnel to align design and construction activities</li><li>Participate in coordination meetings and 3D review sessions to resolve design and construction issues</li><li>Ensure all drawings and models comply with Singapore authorities' standards and regulatory requirements</li><li>Conduct simple QS and layout checks to monitor project progress and maintain accuracy</li><li>Execute additional tasks as assigned to support smooth company operations </li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering</li><li>Relevant Safety certifications / BCSS accreditation</li><li>Minimum 5 years experience drafting for HDB projects, preferably within Singapore-based electrical engineering firms</li><li>Proficient in AutoCAD, REVIT, Navisworks, and MS Office </li><li>Effective communication skills to coordinate with multidisciplinary teams</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>This position reports directly to the Company Director</li><li>6-day work week with alternate Saturdays off</li></ul>",
